 \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi \sigma^2}} e^{-(x+\mu)^2 / \sigma^2} dx = 1 
\exp(-x^2)
\int_{-\infty}^{+\infty} \exp(-x^2)dx\cdot\int_{-\infty}^{+\infty}\exp(-y^2)dx = \int_{-\infty}^{+\infty}\int_{-\infty}^{+\infty}\exp(-x^2-y^2)dxdy
\pi
\exp(-x^2)\gt0\,\forall\,x
\int_{-\infty}^{+\infty}\exp(-x^2)\gt0
\int_{-\infty}^{+\infty}\exp(-x^2) = \sqrt{\pi}
